<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3393] Update site docs and javadoc based on max.block.ms changes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3393</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2120&quot; title=&quot;Add a request timeout to NetworkClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2120&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2120&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; deprecated block.on.buffer.full in favor of max.block.ms. This change alters the behavior of the KafkaProducer. Users may not be expecting that change when upgrading from the 0.8.x clients. We should:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Update the KafkaProducer javadoc&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Update the ProducerConfig docs and the generated site docs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add an entry to the 0.9 upgrade notes (if appropriate)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Related discussion can be seen here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1058&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1058&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
